# 2D RVE: 100x100 mm box, periodic placement (the placer wraps disks across
# the box; the downstream generator is set non-periodic so disks crossing
# the boundary appear clipped).
# Disks via Fuller grading; in 2D mode `fraction` is interpreted as area fraction.
#@output packing.dat
#@box 2 0.1 0.1
# Periodic packing — disks can wrap or cross the rect faces. The generator
# handles boundary-crossing disks via per-intersection anchor pairs on the
# face (see Grid::generateInclusionBoundaryAnchors), so wall clearance is
# not required. Disk-vs-disk overlap, however, must leave room for both
# ITZ rings plus a `diam` mesh-spacing buffer — so the placer requires a
# centre-to-centre gap of `r1 + r2 + diam + 2 * itz`. Tune `#@diam` /
# `#@itz` to match the mesher's `#@diam` and `#@inclusionfile … itz`.
#@periodicity 2 1 1
#@seed 42
#@maxiter 1000
#@diam 0.002
#@itz 1.e-4
#@grading dmin 0.005 dmax 0.012 fraction 0.30
